definition.value: The exact number may be one or two different from the 2n number and still be classified as diploidy (although with aneuploidy). Nearly all mammals are diploid organisms, although all individuals have some small fraction of cells that are polyploidy.
Unipotent cells have the quality of self-renewal which distinguishes them from non-stem cells.
Less potent than multipotent, often thought of as precursor or progenitor cell status.
